11/08/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The US government has allocated $1.3m in aid for mine clearing projects in Serbia, according to an announcement from the US Embassy in Belgrade on Wednesday (10 August). 
The projects are being run in co-operation with the International Trust for Demining and Mine Victims Assistance and the Serbian government.
In other news Wednesday, the Serbia-Montenegro Defence Ministry said that the federal union's army chief, General Major Dragan Paskas, would meet with outgoing KFOR Commander Lieutenant General Yves de Kermabon on Friday. 
The talks are expected to focus on the situations in Kosovo and southern Serbia, as well as bilateral co-operation. 
(Tanjug - 10/08/05)
